Foot and mouth disease, Myanmar
-------------------------------
Information received on 26 Nov 2019 from Dr Ye Tun Win, chief veterinary officer, director general, Livestock Breeding and Veterinary Department, Ministry of Livestock and Fisheries, Nay Pyi Taw, Myanmar

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 1 Oct 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 10 Oct 2019
Report date: 25 Nov 2019
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2 Jul 2018
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (13)
[The 13 outbreaks of FMDV-O occurred in Sagaing (10) and Magway (2) regions and Shan State (1). Details of each outbreak can be seen at the source URL above. - Mod.CRD]

Summary of outbreaks
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 3699 / 523 / 11 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 14 / 0.3 / 2.1 / 0.3
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive; illegal movement of animals; contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering; fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc)

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; traceability; zoning; disinfection; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
Biosecurity Level 2 Diagnostic Laboratory, Shwemyo (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 10 Oct 2019 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 10 Oct 2019 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 10 Oct 2019 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 17 Oct 2019 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 23 Oct 2019 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 30 Oct 2019 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 30 Oct 2019 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 5 Nov 2019 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 13 Nov 2019 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

